I showed this to my 8 year old son that loves playing football, basketball, and baseball and I asked him what it meant to him and he looked and said I have to be the best teammate that he can be and it's never just about him.

The best teammates that I ever competed with, and my best competitors, were those who spent as much or more time being engaged in their teammates' efforts, performances, and play, as they did their own. Champions inspire others, and never ever take all the credit for themselves. That's how it is. Believe it. Live it. Pass it on.
